## Conventions (delete this section if your global instructions already cover these — keep them here only when they need to override globals)

- **Commits**: Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`)
- **No AI attribution**: Never add `Co-Authored-By` or similar trailers to commits unless explicitly asked.
- **Comments**: Default to none. Only write a comment when the WHY is non-obvious.
- **Tests**: Real database / network when feasible; mock only at system boundaries.
- **Secrets**: Never in source. Never in MEMORY.md. Credentials Manager only.

